==English==

===Etymology===
From {{OE.}} {{term|hlysnan}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|lĭs'ən}}, {{IPA|/ˈlɪsən/}}, {{SAMPA|/"lIs@n/}}
* {{audio|en-us-listen.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪsən}}
* {{hyphenation|lis|ten}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{intransitive}} To pay [[attention]] to a [[sound]], to [[note]].
#: ''Please '''listen''' carefully as I explain.''
#: ''I like '''to listen''' to music.''
# {{intransitive}} To [[wait]] for a [[sound]], such as a [[signal]].
#: ''You should '''listen''' for the starting gun.''
# {{intransitive}} To [[accept]] or [[obey]] [[oral]] instruction.
#: ''Good children '''listen''' to their parents.''
# {{transitive|archaic}} To [[hear]] (something), to pay attention to something said.
#* '''1592''', [[w:William Shakespeare|Shakespeare]], ''[[s:The First Part of King Henry the Sixth|1 Hen VI]]: v 3''
#*: ''Lady, vouchsafe '''to listen''' what I say.''

